<p>To indicate that an event may only happen on alternating weeks, 
enter a 2 in the "occurs every" field and either a 0 or a 1 in the "occurs on" field. 
(The "occurs on" field will determine if the event happens on "even" or "odd" weeks where the number of weeks since an old arbitrary date is used.)
This same approach works if you need to designate a different number of weeks that two. 
For example, to indicate something happens every third week, enter 3 in the "occurs every" field and a 0, 1, or 2 in the "occurs on" field.
(Note that every two weeks is not the same as twice per month since most month contain extra days.
Likewise, even and odd weeks do not refer to the week number in a year, since some years contain an odd number of weeks.)</p>
